+# OPENPATCH Agent Gateway v4 Candidate
 
-This package is a candidate iteration for a private/local OPENPATCH fork used as a multi-agent artifact gateway.
+This package is a candidate iteration for a private/local OPENPATCH fork used as a multi-agent artifact gateway across many ChatGPT/Web AI pages, browser profiles, key aliases, and GitHub archive repositories.
 
-## What changed in v3
+## What changed in v4
 
-✅ Added archive-only RoundPack upload path in the extension.
-✅ Added `upload_receipt.json`, `archive_manifest.json`, and `index/latest/<project>.json` generation.
-✅ Added route context fields for project/round/repo/key aliases.
-✅ Added page event trigger API so Auto Continue or another page script can trigger an existing button by `buttonId` or file name.
-✅ Added local bridge MVP skeleton for local status/receipt management.
-✅ Added new unit tests for RoundPack helper functions and archive upload flow.
-✅ Existing patch upload flow is preserved for compatibility.
+✅ Local Bridge upgraded with route resolution, latest, queue, SHA duplicate index, and richer receipts.  
+✅ Added `openpatch-ledger-cli.mjs` so Codex/agents can query `health/routes/status/latest/queue/sha-index/resolve/enqueue`.  
+✅ Extension manifest now allows local bridge hosts (`127.0.0.1` / `localhost`).  
+✅ Extension archive upload posts sanitized receipt to local bridge after GitHub upload.  
+✅ Page event API adds route resolution and bridge status checks.  
+✅ Agent marker schema version moved to `openpatch.agent_button.v4`.  
+✅ Added validate-roundpack GitHub workflow draft for archive-only validation.  
+✅ Self-tests cover npm check, bridge smoke test, route resolver, queue, latest, sha-index, duplicate SHA.
 
 ## Current decision
 
 ⚠️ Candidate package for review and further iteration.
 
-It is not a final install/release package yet. The next iterations should connect route profiles more deeply, add queue/retry, and add local bridge key-alias integration.
+This is not a final multi-browser production install package. The next high-value iteration is moving GitHub upload execution from the extension into the Local Bridge, so multiple key aliases and repo aliases can be managed locally instead of inside browser UI storage.
 
 ## Default use
 
-Use this as an implementation candidate for:
-
 ```text
 Web AI files / RoundPack attachments
 → OPENPATCH button marker + event API
-→ archive-only upload to GitHub ledger repo
-→ receipt/latest/result feedback
-→ Codex/agent reads status and continues
+→ route profile resolver
+→ archive-only upload / receipt
+→ Local Bridge latest + sha-index + queue
+→ Codex/agent queries status and continues
 ```
+
+## Fast entry points
